YENAGOA – The Bayelsa State Governor, Douye Diri, has condemned the killing of one Michael Isaiah during the conduct of the Peoples Democratic Party’s primary for the House Representatives and state Houses of Assembly elections in the state on Sunday. The victim was murdered in Ogbia town in the Constituency One of the Ogbia Local Government Area. Diri, who spoke through a statement by his Director, New Media, Kola Oredipe, described the incident as an isolated case in the exercise. -Advertisement- He said it was an orchestrated attempt by certain desperate persons to undermine the generally peaceful conduct of the primaries across the state. The governor, therefore, called on the security agencies to investigate the cowardly killing and ensure that perpetrators were arrested and made to face the full weight of the law. He said that the PDP remained a peaceful party and would not condone such dastardly acts in the name of politics. The governor expressed his condolences to the immediate family of the deceased and assured them that justice would be served in this case.